'''Scott Barrett''' is the former production programmer for all [[LucasOnline]] sites. He started at [[LucasArts]] in [[2000]] and created lucasarts.com and the gaming sites. Moving on in [[2001]], he started working for [[Lucasfilm]] and built fully all the HTML/stylesheet templates, JavaScript libraries and all flash objects as well as being an integral part in implementing the applications on all LucasOnline sites including [[StarWars.com]], blogs.starwars.com, forums.starwars.com, lucasarts.com, indianajones.com, [[HoloNet News (original website)|holonetnews.com]], and thx1138movie.com.

Scott left Lucasfilm in May [[2006]] to pursue a job as senior web technologist at Francis Ford Coppola Presents.

